location: raleigh, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Avoid the guy that has the m1 garand listed with the drift wood(with indian carved into it) as the background. He claims to have a CMP certificate but he REFUSES to meet in person, he can ONLY ship. He wants a check cash or money order because "my job does not allow me to leave".(Somehow he cant meet for 5 minutes to do a sale but he can pack a gun and run to the post office.. rigggght)

I offered the guy to meet in NC(where his last ad was at) and he flat refused it, I offered him $100 extra to meet me in person and he still refused. When I talked to him on the phone he could not speak english(sounded chinese to me) but he could text and email perfectly fine in english.

His ad was later flagged as a scam so he TEXTS me and tells me "im going to come blow your brains out you ***hole" and "you suck, you ruined this for me".

This guy is a con.. He is now posting his rifle for $300 more but in the Minnesota craigslist..(amazing how he is to busy working to meet me for 5 minutes but could end up in MN not 24 hours later...) Watch out for this piece of work. SEND HIM NOTHING because its a 100% con.

His current armslist listing is 2656140 (see numbers in link top of page in address bar). Flag this Rtard as a scam!

We need to drive scum like this off armslist and make it clear this is not craigslist! Ever since the gun panic, scum leeches of society like this has been eyeballing gun owners as a juicy steak to screw over.. 

Thanks for reading this and hopefully flagging that guys ads.

title: For Sale:  IWI Tavor SAR Bullpup Rifle TSFD18, 5.56 Nato, 18 in, Semi-Auto, Gas Piston, Syn Stock, Flat Dark Earth Finish, 30 Rds
location: Will ship to FFL or in store pick up, Nebraska, United States
postcontent:
The TAVOR is a perfect fusion of an ordnance grade steel receiver coupled to a Mil-Spec cold hammer forged barrel and encased into a high-impact strength polymer uni-body with exceptional situational ergonomics. The ultra-compact form factor allows for easy transitions in close quarter situations…or even in your favorite deer blind. The bullpup design moves the center of gravity of the rifle closer to the users’ body allowing for more instinctive aiming and improved acquisition time to target. This innovative design also allows for a full length barrel, which means no loss of down range ballistic accuracy. Near and far range accuracy is enhanced by the minimized recoil provided by a non-lubricated long stroke gas piston system. With the exception of a hand-specific locking bolt, the rifle is completely ambidextrous allowing for easy left-hand conversion of the operating handle, ejection port, fire-control safety, sling swivel receptacles and fore-mounted accessory Picatinny rail. The TAVOR® is supplied with IDF-tested and approved magazines – but you can also use your own AR-15/M16 style magazines.

Rifle package comes with 1-30 round magazine, lock and cleaning kit.

title: For Sale:  50 Cal Beowulf
postcontent:
This is a very impressive gun. It has a 24" barrel, Bushmaster lower receiver, it has the pepper pot muzzle brake, a Midwest Industries hand guard, an adjustable butt stock and a bi-pod. It has been professionally finished with Cerakote.

Although much has been written about its tactical uses, the .50 Beowulf is gaining recognition as a sporting cartridge. By virtue of its ballistics which are similar or superior to those of the venerable .45-70 Government[6] cartridge it is becoming more widely recognized as being usable for a wide variety of North American game, including deer, moose and black bear.

The cartridge utilizes a rebated rim, sized to match the rim of the 7.62x39mm and 6.5 mm Grendel rounds. The case body is very similar in dimensions to the .500 S&W Magnum revolver cartridge, being slightly longer and fully tapered for automatic feeding in the weapon.
The round is intended to improve stopping power greatly at short- to medium-range as compared to the standard 5.56x45mm NATO round. One of its advertised uses is at vehicle checkpoints, since the heavy bullet's flight path is not easily deflected by auto glass or standard vehicle body panels.

title: For Sale:  Is it really a pre ban gun?
location: Winston Greensboro highpoint, North Carolina, United States
postcontent:
A pre ban weapon will have all its original features such as bayonet and the mount it screw to
Clinton ban weapons have the bayonet mount ground off frequently they have thumb hole stocks ban weapons also have an importers stamp on the receiver or barrel ban weapons imported under the ban needed some American made parts installed as well 
Post ban imports have all their original equipment and a import mark
It does not matter when the gun was made what matters is when it was imported so the long and short of it is that the ban produced several variants that can be worth mmore
 than any preban don't pay more for an alleged preban  if that SKS has a ugly yellow thumb hole stock and no bayonet It is a ban weapon not a preban don't get ripped off

title: For Sale:  Glock Barrel Gold Titanium Nitride Barrel Coating 17 19 26 34 22 23 27 35 21 30
postcontent:
Up for sale is a Titanium Nitride finish for the Glock barrel of your choice (Other makes may be substituted, just contact us) by MG Precision Arms LTD (https://www.facebook.com/MGPrecisionArms). The barrel will be cleaned, refinished and then coated. The turn around time will be under 3 weeks from the time we receive the barrel. It is usually even much shorter than that. We offer better pricing, better quality and a faster turn around than any of our competitors. 

For those not familiar with Titanium Nitride it is unique in terms of firearm finishes as it not only gives a custom look to your firearm it also adds durability and reduces the friction on the coated part. This allows you to run your firearm with less oil/lube, vastly increases the durability, and makes cleaning much easier. Another plus with Titanium Nitride is the average coating only adds 3 micrometers of material, so it will not change the function of your firearm only enhance the look and performance of it. It is applied in a cathodic arc chamber which ensures a uniform coating. This is the same coating that is used by high speed cutting tools to give you an idea of its strength.

If you have any questions please let us know. Thanks for taking the time to look!

Frequently Asked Questions:
1. What other colors do you offer? We offer gold, rose, carbon black and silver.
2. Does this include a barrel? No, this is for the coating of your existing barrel. Once you purchase, we will send you the information on where to send your barrel.
3. Can you coat threaded barrels? Yes we can, it doesn't alter the threads and actually offers them some protection.
4. Can you coat aftermarket barrels? Yes we can, in fact aftermarket barrels coatings are a large part of our business.
5. Can you coat my slide or other small parts? We can coat any part that is steel, stainless steel, or titanium. We do not coat aluminum. Contact us for more information.
6. Does this coat the inside of the barrel? If will coat inside the crown and chamber, the areas where most wear occurs.
7. Is there any difference in the colors hardness? No, they are all equally durable and in the 80-90 range on the Rockwell Scale. The Titanium Nitride is much more durable than the steel it coats.
